# User Role Can Be Modified in User Profile

## Vulnerability Type
Broken Access Control

## Difficulty
Apprentice

## Platform
PortSwigger Web Security Academy

## Goal
Solve the lab by accessing the admin panel and deleting the user "carlos".

## Root Cause
The application trusted user-controlled JSON input and failed to enforce proper server-side authorization checks. Administrative privileges were determined using the `roleid` parameter, which could be modified by the user.

## Exploitation Steps
1. Browse the application
2. Log in with normal user credentials
3. Intercept the profile update request using Burp Suite
4. Identify the JSON request body
5. Add or modify the parameter `"roleid": 2`
6. Forward the modified request
7. Access the `/admin` panel
8. Delete the user "carlos"

## Impact
An attacker can escalate privileges by modifying user-controlled parameters and gain unauthorized administrative access.

## Prevention
- Enforce authorization checks on the server side
- Do not trust client-controlled input
- Validate role assignments securely
- Restrict sensitive parameters from user modification

## What I Learned
This lab helped me understand how insecure handling of user-controlled JSON parameters can lead to privilege escalation and unauthorized administrative access.
